juniProfileMIB.name: juniProfileMIB

revisions.description: Added atm1483(11) to JuniProfileIfEncaps TEXTUAL-CONVENTION. Added support for range indexing of profile assignments.
Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.
Added ppp(1), pppoe(17) and any(127) to JuniProfileIfEncaps TEXTUAL-CONVENTION.
Added juniProfAssignIfTable, juniProfToIfMapTable to configure and report assignments of profiles to interface/encapsulation pairs.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniProfileMIB.description: The Profile MIB for the Juniper Networks enterprise.

JuniProfileIfEncaps.name: JuniProfileIfEncaps
JuniProfileIfEncaps.description: Encapsulated protocol type. The 'any' value is a wildcard value. The DESCRIPTION clause for an object having this syntax must describe how the 'any' value applies, if at all.

JuniProfileRangeId.name: JuniProfileRangeId
JuniProfileRangeId.description: An application-specific identifier used to distinguish multiple profile assignments on a given interface/encapsulation pair. Not all interface applications support this capability. The semantics of the identifier are governed by the interface application on which a profile is assigned. For example, the ATM AAL5 application defines the semantics for range identifiers used in profile assignments on ATM AAL5 interfaces; and might choose to associate range identifiers with distinct VPI/VCI ranges. The value zero is reserved for use as the range identifier value for profile assignments on interfaces that do not support more than one assignment per encapsulation.

juniProfileNameTable.name: juniProfileNameTable
juniProfileNameTable.description: The entries in this table provide mappings of configuration profile names to local integer identifiers for those profiles. These integers are used as indexes into other MIB tables containing profile configuration parameters associated with the same profile name.

juniProfileNameEntry.name: juniProfileNameEntry
juniProfileNameEntry.description: A mapping of a profile name to an integer identifier for that name.

juniProfileNameName.name: juniProfileNameName
juniProfileNameName.description: The profile name uniquely identifying this entry.

juniProfileNameRowStatus.name: juniProfileNameRowStatus
juniProfileNameRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only the values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' may be SET.

juniProfileNameId.name: juniProfileNameId
juniProfileNameId.description: The integer identifier associated with this profile name. This value of this identifier is assigned by the device when an entry in this table is created.

juniProfileIdTable.name: juniProfileIdTable
juniProfileIdTable.description: Provides inverse mapping of profile IDs to profile names.

juniProfileIdEntry.name: juniProfileIdEntry
juniProfileIdEntry.description: A mapping of an integer identifier to a profile name.

juniProfileIdId.name: juniProfileIdId
juniProfileIdId.description: The integer identifier associated with this profile name.

juniProfileIdName.name: juniProfileIdName
juniProfileIdName.description: The profile name having the associated identifier.

juniProfAssignIfTable.name: juniProfAssignIfTable
juniProfAssignIfTable.description: Table providing profile assignment to interface/encapsulation pair. The entries in this table specify which profile to use when creating and configuring a dynamic interface (whose type is identified by the encapsulation) above a specified interface. Each entry in this table is reflected in a juniProfAssignIfTable entry having a zero-valued range identifier.

juniProfAssignIfEntry.name: juniProfAssignIfEntry
juniProfAssignIfEntry.description: An assignment of a profile to an interface/encapsulation pair.

juniProfAssignIfIndex.name: juniProfAssignIfIndex
juniProfAssignIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface to which the profile is assigned.

juniProfAssignIfEncaps.name: juniProfAssignIfEncaps
juniProfAssignIfEncaps.description: The encapsulated protocol type to which the assigned profile pertains. An interface may have a different profile assigned for each encapsulation it supports. If an entry for a specific encapsulation is absent, the profile assigned for the 'any' encapsulation will be used (if that assignment is present in this table).

juniProfAssignIfRowStatus.name: juniProfAssignIfRowStatus
juniProfAssignIfRowStatus.description: For SET, supports only createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). Returns active(1) when read.

juniProfAssignIfProfileId.name: juniProfAssignIfProfileId
juniProfAssignIfProfileId.description: The ID of the profile assigned to this interface/encapsulation pair.

juniProfToIfMapTable.name: juniProfToIfMapTable
juniProfToIfMapTable.description: Table to report the set of interface/encapsulation pairs assigned to each profile.

juniProfToIfMapEntry.name: juniProfToIfMapEntry
juniProfToIfMapEntry.description: Reports an interface/encapsulation pair assigned to a profile.

juniProfToIfMapProfileId.name: juniProfToIfMapProfileId
juniProfToIfMapProfileId.description: The ID of the profile assigned to this interface/encapsulation pair.

juniProfToIfMapIndex.name: juniProfToIfMapIndex
juniProfToIfMapIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface to which the profile is assigned.

juniProfToIfMapEncaps.name: juniProfToIfMapEncaps
juniProfToIfMapEncaps.description: The encapsulation type to which the assigned profile pertains. An interface may have a different profile assigned for each encapsulation type it supports.

juniProfAssignIfRangeTable.name: juniProfAssignIfRangeTable
juniProfAssignIfRangeTable.description: Table providing profile assignment to interface/encapsulation/range 3-tuple. The entries in this table specify which profile to use when creating and configuring a dynamic interface (whose type is identified by the encapsulation) above a specified interface, with profile selection being further discriminated by the range identifier. Each entry in juniProfAssignIfTable is reflected by an entry in this table having a zero-valued range identifier.

juniProfAssignIfRangeEntry.name: juniProfAssignIfRangeEntry
juniProfAssignIfRangeEntry.description: An assignment of a profile to an interface/encapsulation/range 3-tuple.

juniProfAssignIfRangeIndex.name: juniProfAssignIfRangeIndex
juniProfAssignIfRangeIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface to which the profile is assigned.

juniProfAssignIfRangeEncaps.name: juniProfAssignIfRangeEncaps
juniProfAssignIfRangeEncaps.description: The encapsulated protocol type to which the assigned profile pertains. An interface may have zero, one or more profiles assigned for each encapsulation it supports. If an entry for a specific encapsulation is absent, the profile assigned for the 'any' encapsulation will be used (if that assignment is present in this table).

juniProfAssignIfRangeRangeId.name: juniProfAssignIfRangeRangeId
juniProfAssignIfRangeRangeId.description: An application-specific range identifier to which the assigned profile pertains. An interface may have zero, one or more profiles assigned for each encapsulation it supports, distinguished by range identifier. A value of zero should be used for an interface that does not support multiple profile assignments per encapsulation.

juniProfAssignIfRangeRowStatus.name: juniProfAssignIfRangeRowStatus
juniProfAssignIfRangeRowStatus.description: For SET, supports only createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). Returns active(1) when read.

juniProfAssignIfRangeProfileId.name: juniProfAssignIfRangeProfileId
juniProfAssignIfRangeProfileId.description: The ID of the profile assigned to this interface/encapsulation/range 3-tuple.

juniProfToIfRangeMapTable.name: juniProfToIfRangeMapTable
juniProfToIfRangeMapTable.description: Table to report the set of interface/encapsulation/range 3-tuples assigned to each profile.

juniProfToIfRangeMapEntry.name: juniProfToIfRangeMapEntry
juniProfToIfRangeMapEntry.description: Reports an interface/encapsulation/range 3-tuple assigned to a profile.

juniProfToIfRangeMapProfileId.name: juniProfToIfRangeMapProfileId
juniProfToIfRangeMapProfileId.description: The ID of the profile assigned to this interface/encapsulation pair.

juniProfToIfRangeMapIndex.name: juniProfToIfRangeMapIndex
juniProfToIfRangeMapIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface to which the profile is assigned.

juniProfToIfRangeMapEncaps.name: juniProfToIfRangeMapEncaps
juniProfToIfRangeMapEncaps.description: The encapsulation type to which the assigned profile pertains. An interface may have zero, one or more profiles assigned for each encapsulation type it supports.

juniProfToIfRangeMapRangeId.name: juniProfToIfRangeMapRangeId
juniProfToIfRangeMapRangeId.description: An application-specific range identifier to which the assigned profile pertains. An interface may have zero, one or more profiles assigned for each encapsulation it supports, distinguished by range identifier.

juniProfileCompliance.name: juniProfileCompliance
juniProfileCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting naming of configuration profiles. This statement became obsolete when the interface profile assignment group was added.

juniProfileCompliance2.name: juniProfileCompliance2
juniProfileCompliance2.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting naming of configuration profiles and profile assignment to interfaces. This statement became obsolete when support for range indexing of profile assignments was added.

juniProfileCompliance3.name: juniProfileCompliance3
juniProfileCompliance3.description: The compliance statement for systems supporting naming of configuration profiles and profile assignment to interfaces.

juniProfileGroup.name: juniProfileGroup
juniProfileGroup.description: The basic collection of objects providing management of Profile naming functionality in a Juniper product.

juniProfileIfGroup.name: juniProfileIfGroup
juniProfileIfGroup.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of Profile assignment to interfaces in a Juniper product. This group became obsolete when support for range indexing of profile assignments was added.

juniProfileIfGroup2.name: juniProfileIfGroup2
juniProfileIfGroup2.description: The basic collection of objects providing management of Profile assignment to interfaces in a Juniper product.
